09/08/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Quoting sources at the General Prosecutor's Office, the ATA news agency reported Sunday (8 August) that there will be new arrests as a result of the security forces' Compass Operation, aimed at cracking down on drug trafficking. The operation is being conducted in co-operation with Italian police and prosecutors. It is also receiving support from the Tirana prosecutor's office and the public order ministry's criminal police department, the sources said. (ATA - 08/08/04)
